  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/psychopy--psychopy",
  "meta": {
    "title": "PsychoPy",
    "description": "For running psychology and neuroscience experiments",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-11T02:04:07.362Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11T02:04:07.362Z",
    "keywords": [
      "experiment",
      "experiment-control",
      "experimental-design",
      "linguistics",
      "neuroscience",
      "psycholinguistics",
      "psychology",
      "psychophysics",
      "psychopy",
      "python",
      "science"
    ],
    "license": "GPL-3.0"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "[![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/psychopy.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/PsychoPy)\n[![Contributor Covenant](https://img.shields.io/badge/Contributor%20Covenant-v1.4%20adopted-ff69b4.svg)](code-of-conduct.md)",
    "context": "[![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/psychopy.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/PsychoPy)\n[![Contributor Covenant](https://img.shields.io/badge/Contributor%20Covenant-v1.4%20adopted-ff69b4.svg)](code-of-conduct.md)  \n\n---\n\nPsychoPy is an open-source package for creating experiments in behavioral science. It aims to provide a single package that is:\n\n* precise enough for psychophysics\n* easy enough for teaching\n* flexible enough for everything else\n* able to run experiments in a local Python script or online in JavaScript\n\nTo meet these goals PsychoPy provides a choice of interface - you can use a\nsimple graphical user interface called Builder, or write your experiments in\nPython code. The entire application and library are written in Python and is\nplatform independent.\n\n**Note:** this repository now contains _only_ the PsychoPy _library_. The code for the application user interface \nis now in separate repositories for \n[PsychoPy Studio](https://github.com/psychopy/psychopy-studio) (for the modern web-based GUI) \nand [PsychoPy App](https://github.com/psychopy/psychopy-app) (for the legacy wxPython GUI).\n\nThere is a range of documentation at:\n\n* [PsychoPy Homepage](https://www.psychopy.org)\n* [Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLFB5A1BE51964D587)\n* The textbook, [Building Experiments in PsychoPy](https://uk.sagepub.com/en-gb/eur/building-experiments-in-psychopy/book253480)\n* [The discourse user forum](https://discourse.psychopy.org)",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
  "domains": [
    "lang:python"
  ],
